<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="192" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1435,1533,2036]" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,338,1533,1556]" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">Description.</emphasis>
Habitus as in 
<figureCitation box="[511,618,1533,1556]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1859,1881]" captionTargetBox="[234,1410,211,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[155,1432,194,1836]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Habitus, 1–2: Pelthydrus ruiliensis sp. nov. 3–4: Pelthydrus madli Schönmann. 1, 3 dorsal view; 2, 4 ventral view. Scale=1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1294267/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">Figs. 1–2</figureCitation>
. BL: 
<quantity box="[687,851,1533,1556]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.825" metricValueMax="2.95" metricValueMin="2.7" pageId="3" pageNumber="192" unit="mm" value="2.825" valueMax="2.95" valueMin="2.7">2.70–2.95 mm</quantity>
; BW: 
<quantity box="[928,1091,1533,1556]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.575" metricValueMax="1.65" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="192" unit="mm" value="1.575" valueMax="1.65" valueMin="1.5">1.50–1.65 mm</quantity>
. Body elongated oval, slightly convex, semicircular in posterior portion, surface shiny, dark black; antennae, lateral margins of pronotum, labial palpi, maxillary palpi, tibiae and tarsi yellowish brown. Head trapezoidal, about 1.6 times as wide as long; surface microreticulate, with evenly distributed median-sized punctures and yellowish brown setae sparsely distributed around eyes; frontoclypeal suture distinct; anterior margin of clypeus somewhat arched in the middle. Pronotum trapezoidal, about 1.4 times as wide as long, anterior corners rounded, the lateral margins nearly straight; surface microreticulate around corners; median-sized ground punctures evenly distributed; yellowish brown setae sparsely distributed along lateral margins of anterior half. Elytra about 2.6 times as long as wide; broadest part at basal 0.4, then gradually narrowed posteriorly, ending with narrowly rounded apices that do not meet at midline; ground punctures which slightly larger than those on head densely distributed, serial punctures on both sides of elytra. Ventral surface reddish brown, mentum dark brown, somewhat rugulose; prosternum reddish brown with a median longitudinal carina; Mesoventrite with apically slightly rounded triangular plate and median longitudinal carina; metaventrite with a posterior teardrop-shaped, flat and smooth glabrous area; first sternite with a medial longitudinal carina not reaching posterior margin. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[1355,1422,1917,1940]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–6" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1970,1992]" captionTargetBox="[257,1430,695,1903]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[166,1430,668,1938]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 5–6. Aedeagus, dorsal view; 5. Pelthydrus ruiliensis sp. nov. (holotype); 6. Pelthydrus madli Schönmann. Scale=0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1294269/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). 
<quantity box="[151,249,1949,1972]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.2" pageId="3" pageNumber="192" unit="mm" value="0.52">0.52 mm</quantity>
long, nearly parallel-sided, parameres about 1.4 times as long as phallobase; median lobe wide, gradually narrowing from base, gonopore located at apex; parameres exceeding median lobe, with apex oblique and truncated, inner margin shorter than outer margin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
